Movie: My Best Friend Is a Vampire

Review: Once again I return to Yami douga to watch several mediocre ghost stories so I can be rewarded with one which will keep me up at night
I want to be besties with the little old girl, she seems so polite ☺️
An improvement when compared to the fourth installment but that isn't really saying much. This one had a lot of good ideas but felt like it was lacking in delivery.
Probably the weakest entry in the series so far, with no particular segments which stood out to me. Just a bit boring tbh
Nothing is particularly standing out about this one besides the guy in the first clip making the first sensible decision in the series by running as soon as things got spooky.
The second instalment of the Yami Douga anthology series. This one was a bit hit or miss for me but when it hit, damn it hit hard.
Uhhh Intricate rituals, woman edition, i guess

Movie: The Lair of the White Worm

Review: A simply spooky anthology of found footage horror, Yami Douga is nothing special but it doesn't need to be anything more.Excited to watch the remainder of the series.

Movie: The Gods Have a Nervous Breakdown

Review: I have no clue what this film was trying to do. Bizarre and campy, this could potentially be a film so bad it's entertaining but it's too slow and the plot doesn't really go anywhere. Despite the story supposedly being about vampire brothers in a haunted forest, the film barely plays into any horror elements at all instead focusing on mystery and drama. This would be fine if the mystery were any good.Instead, we watch our characters meander between…
Within the first five minutes of this film, a dude's dick gets bitten off, and if that isn't peak cinema I don't know what is.
